<subSubSection id="2B996578FFFCFFF01ED138D3FB2BFD2C" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFFCFFF01ED138D3FF5AFE68" blockId="40.[189,248,459,485]" box="[189,248,459,485]" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">
<heading id="3874819FFFFCFFF01ED138D3FF5AFE68" bold="true" box="[189,248,459,485]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" reason="3">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01ED138D3FF5AFE68" bold="true" box="[189,248,459,485]" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">Note</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFFCFFF01ED138E1FB2BFD2C" blockId="40.[187,1399,505,673]" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">
This species lacks the typical cheliceral teeth that are still considered as a diagnostic feature for 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFFCFFF01ED13B04FECCFDBB" authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1871" box="[189,366,540,566]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Stephanopinae">Stephanopinae</taxonomicName>
. Instead, its elongated labium and peglike-setae on endites (see 
<bibRefCitation id="07124B02FFFCFFF01A243B04FA85FDBA" author="Teixeira R. A. &amp; Campos L. A. &amp; Lise A. A." box="[1096,1319,540,567]" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" pagination="65 - 78" refId="ref21299" refString="Teixeira R. A., Campos L. A. &amp; Lise A. A. 2014. Phylogeny of Aphantochilinae and Strophiinae sensu Simon (Araneae; Thomisidae). Zoologica Scripta 43 (1): 65 - 78. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zsc. 12036" type="journal article" year="2014">
Teixeira 
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01AC73B05FB44FDBB" box="[1195,1254,540,566]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
) allow us to undoubtedly consider this spider as an Aphantochilinae. We propose the transfer of 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFFCFFF01AA73B58FAD4FDD7" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1942" box="[1227,1398,576,602]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Stephanopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quimiliensis">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01AA73B58FAD4FDD7" box="[1227,1398,576,602]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">S. quimiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFFCFFF01EB03B7BFE53FDF0" authority="Simon, 1866" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1866" box="[220,497,611,637]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Ulocymus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01EB03B7BFEF3FDF0" box="[220,337,611,637]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">Ulocymus</emphasis>
Simon, 1866
</taxonomicName>
based on the presence of stout and conical projections on the dorsum of the carapace (see 
<bibRefCitation id="07124B02FFFCFFF01F0E3B9EFDE4FD2D" author="Teixeira R. A. &amp; Campos L. A. &amp; Lise A. A." box="[354,582,646,673]" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" pagination="65 - 78" refId="ref21299" refString="Teixeira R. A., Campos L. A. &amp; Lise A. A. 2014. Phylogeny of Aphantochilinae and Strophiinae sensu Simon (Araneae; Thomisidae). Zoologica Scripta 43 (1): 65 - 78. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zsc. 12036" type="journal article" year="2014">
Teixeira 
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01FAB3B9FFE59FD2D" box="[455,507,646,672]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
) and shape of the copulatory structures (
<figureCitation id="FBB82A76FFFCFFF01A4F3B9EFBD9FD2C" box="[1059,1147,646,673]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="38.[188,231,1956,1982]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,733,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-58@38.[187,1398,733,1915]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="Fig. 25. Stephanopis quimiliensis Mello-Leitão, 1942. Holotype, ♂ (MLP 15455). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Front. C–D. Left palp. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view." pageId="40" pageNumber="66">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
